{
  "stem": "2684.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that saved my life-- again, something from upstairs, and I couldn't eat.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I don't know when.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "A day later, an hour later, or a week later, they took me to a hospital, which hospital was in the German part of-- see, Dachau was the largest-- not concentration camp, was the first concentration camp in Germany.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was built 15 kilometer from Munich.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "First for prisoner and later on for Jews and so forth.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it was full of barracks of textile where they-- where they provided for the soldiers.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They're full of medicine.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "After we got free, then we come physically, we went around to organizing-- which means stealing-- whatever we could find, eat, and clothes, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we find a tremendous amount of clothes, cloth-- German officer cloth-- by the 10,000 and 10,000 of meters.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we find medicine, we don't know what.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We didn't touch.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it was in capsules and pill forms, and buildings full of them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they took me to the hospital, and they started treat me as they treat a guy with fleck typhus.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And fortunately, something helped.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know what was it, medicine, I don't really remember anything of that couple of weeks I spend there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "All I know is they discharged me and I was still a walking corpse, but I was already a little bit better because they fed you there.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Maybe intravenously, I don't know what they did.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I can't-- Was this the American soldiers?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This American, yeah, yeah.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now by the time that I realized, because they never take me back to the lager where we were, they take us to the lager where the guards was staying, which mean we went into the German lager.",
      "word_count": 38
    }
  ],
